  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-05-23",
    "date": "2020-06-26T15:57:53Z",
    "text": "Veterans' Credit Protection Act\n\n This bill directs the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to conduct outreach to inform veterans of how to resolve credit issues caused by a delayed payment of a claim for emergency hospital care, medical services, or other emergency health care furnished through a non-VA provider.\n\n The Government Accountability Office shall conduct a study that evaluates the effectiveness of the Office of Community Care in providing timely payment of a proper invoice for such care by the required payment date."
  },
